liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Ange Postecoglou has had a stunning start to life in the Premier League with Spurs - but how good is stunning? Well, it's Tottenham's best start to a season in the English top flight since 1960/61. That team, led by the legendary coach Bill Nicholson, won the Division 1 title that year as well as the FA Cup, becoming the first team to win English football's Double in the 20th century. That was Tottenham's last top-flight title and, although it's important not to get too far ahead of ourselves, Ange does have a history of claiming drought-ending titles. At South Melbourne he broke a seven-year drought, at Yokohoma F Marinos he ended a 15-year barren run and, at Celtic, he ended a lengthy one-year Scottish Premiership drought (everything's relative). No team that has taken 26 points from their first 10 games of a Premier League season (the English top flight since 1992) has finished anywhere lower than third.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Spurs' best start to a season since 1960/61

children.content: Ange Postecoglou has had a stunning start to life in the Premier League with Spurs - but how good is stunning?
Well, it's Tottenham's best start to a season in the English top flight since 1960/61.
That team, led by the legendary coach Bill Nicholson, won the Division 1 title that year as well as the FA Cup, becoming the first team to win English football's Double in the 20th century.
Bill Nicholson, capped once by England, won eight major trophies in his 16-year managerial spell at Spurs between 1958 and 1972.
That was Tottenham's last top-flight title and, although it's important not to get too far ahead of ourselves, Ange does have a history of claiming drought-ending titles.
At South Melbourne he broke a seven-year drought, at Yokohoma F Marinos he ended a 15-year barren run and, at
Celtic, he ended a lengthy one-year Scottish Premiership drought (everything's relative).
No team that has taken 26 points from their first 10 games of a Premier League season (the English top flight since 1992) has finished anywhere lower than third.
